{
  "texts": [
    "Set subtraction is denoted A⧵B.",
    "For singleton B = {b}, set subtraction is simplified to A ⧵ b.",
    "The zero vector is denoted 0 with the vector's dimension implicit from context.",
    "1[a] is the indicator function, where 1[a] = 1 if predicate a is true and 0 otherwise.",
    "Let x ∈ X ⊆ ℝ d denote an arbitrary feature vector, and let y ∈ Y be a dependent value (e.g., label, target)."
